      <content lang="en" title="GeeXboX Sources">
        Here are the GeeXboX 0.98 sources. You need both the wget package and a connection to the Internet to compile your own GeeXboX. Most of the packages are directly downloaded from the web while compiling the GeeXboX. So, here are the sources :<br/><br/>
          <b><use name="dl-src-lite"/> - <use name="dl1-src-lite"/> - <use name="dl2-src-lite"/> - <use name="dl3-src-lite"/> (Lite Package - 127 kB)</b><br/>
          <b><use name="dl-src-full"/> - <use name="dl1-src-full"/> - <use name="dl2-src-full"/> - <use name="dl3-src-full"/> (Full Package - faster connection to the Internet needed - 113 MB)</b>
      </content>
